disabled children. The owner of Joe's Standard Bar put the squeeze
on customers to contribute to help children. But just before
Christmas, Rotolo slipped and hit his head at the City Market. The
76-year-old man ended up in the hospital with a brain injury. How
does a family reconcile itself with the question: Why do bad things
happen to good people? Joe Lambe. 30. Photos.
