</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   VITAL-SIGNS (Undated) _ News and notes on health and fitness:
</P>
<P>
   _ Optimism and self-confidence may prove to be potent weapons in
staving off a recurrence of heart disease, if a new study by
Carnegie Mellon researchers is any indication. Patients in the
study who evidenced a positive outlook, greater self-control and
higher self-esteem after angioplasty surgery were less likely to
suffer a heart attack, undergo bypass surgery, or require a second
angioplasty in the next six months. (265 words)
</P>
<P>
   _ Two women taking Chinese herbal preparations to treat eczema
suffered kidney failure, raising new questions about the safety of
the remedies, according to a report in the British medical journal
The Lancet. (330 words)
</P>
<P>
   _ Chocolate, a new report indicates, contains high levels of
catechins, substances with antioxidant properties that may help
fight cancer and heart disease. (220 words)
</P>
<P>
   _ Supplying oxygen to patients awaiting surgery after suffering
a detached retina may help decrease damage to the eye, according to
a California researcher who has successfully tested his theory on
cats. (300 words)
</P>
