Medicare and increasing spending on the military. But Democrats
argue that the surplus projections are based on a series of
questionable premises: that the economy will avoid a protracted
downturn; that unexplained surges in revenue will continue, and
that the forecasting ability of budget analysts will prove far more
accurate than it has in the past. The biggest problem with the
projections, Democrats say, is that they assume an unrealistically
low level of increases in government spending. By Richard W.
Stevenson.
