into yet another political crisis on Monday by firing of the prime
minister he appointed only three months ago and replacing him with
a man who Yeltsin said should become the troubled country's next
president. Sergei Stepashin, appointed in May, became the fourth
prime minister sacked by Yeltsin in the past 18 months.
