Jordan and Syria have made Wednesday a holiday so people don't have
to be outside. So has the Palestinian Authority, which is warning
people to be inside so they don't hurt their eyes. An
over-reaction? Maybe. But it is a way of protecting people who
don't understand the risks. The Israeli Likud Party is holding a
rally in the Golan Heights, where a lot of people are going to look
at the eclipse, and using it to kick of a campaign to keep the
Golan. DEVELOPING. (Kaplow, Cox News Service).
