Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   PAXSON _ Paxson Communications Corp., owner of the largest U.S.
TV station group, said it hired investment bank Salomon Smith
Barney to explore a possible merger or sale of a stake in the
company. Paxson said its board decided to pursue the moves in
anticipation of last week's ruling by the Federal Communications
Commission that will allow broadcasters to own two TV stations in
one large market. (Haddad, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
