<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Video store puttin' on the glitz for `Shakespeare'
 &HT;    By Bob Longino
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ For never was a video of more glow than this of
Oscar-winner Gwyneth and her co-star Joe.
</P>
<P>
   ``Shakespeare in Love,'' the Gwyneth Paltrow-Joseph Fiennes date
movie that won seven Academy Awards, including best picture,
arrives in video stores today for rental. And it's getting the
royal treatment at the Ansley Mall (Atlanta) Blockbuster.
</P>
<P>
   From 3:30 p.m. to 5:30 p.m. Thursday, Georgia Shakespeare
Festival actress Kathleen McManus will be at the store in full
regalia as Queen Elizabeth I for a trivia contest. Five other
actors from the Festival will perform scenes from ``Romeo and
Juliet,'' ``As You Like It,'' ``A Midsummer Night's Dream'' and
``Henry V.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Every year we do something special for the movie that won all
the awards,'' says Hafeezah Mahdi, assistant manager at the Ansley
Blockbuster.
</P>
<P>
   Many Blockbuster stores are stocking ``Shakespeare'' tapes in
``Titanic'' numbers. The Ansley store, for instance, is expecting
more than 180 copies of ``Shakespeare.'' That's about the same
number it got last year for Leonardo DiCaprio's watery weeper and
roughly 60 more than it received earlier this year for ``Saving
Private Ryan.''
</P>
<P>
   While ``Shakespeare in Love'' is not yet priced to sell _ it
currently costs just over $100 to buy _ DVDs carry a suggested
price of $29.99. The latter includes the movie trailer.
</P>
<P>
   _ Bob Longino writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
