   SLAB CHURCH &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ It took the tears of a 6-year-old to open
Vesta Wilson's heart to the importance of her mission. It was three
years ago when she gave Larry, now 9, a bag of miniature race cars
for his birthday. She hugged him and said, ``Larry, I love you.''
He began to cry. ``Nobody ever told me they loved me,'' he said.
Larry is typical of the nearly 40 children Wilson sees each week at
Sunday School at Church on the Slab. By JAIME JORDAN. Story has
moved in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
