   WRIGHT-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Across America, people are reacting negatively to an
increasing phoniness in American politics. The avalanche of big
private money into political campaigns is not only corrupting
legislation. It's drying up originality and genuineness among
candidates. More and more, the gates to congressional service are
opened to those who can raise big money from private contributors
for television commercials and professional campaign consultants,
and closed to those _ regardless of vision, commitment and ability
_ who cannot. By JIM WRIGHT. Story has moved in ``k'' commentary
category. &QL; 
