<P>
   RUSSIA-POLITICS (Moscow) _ Russian President Yeltsin fires Prime
Minister Stepashin and his Cabinet, apparently in a bid to reassert
his influence in maneuvering over next July's presidential
election. He then names Vladimir Putin, a former spy and head of
the main successor agency to the KGB. Putin, who is likely to be
