   NY-POLICE-COMPLAINTS (New York) _ In what would be a marked
change in its much-criticized disciplinary procedure, the Police
Department is discussing reducing its role in re-investigating
allegations of misconduct by officers whose behavior has already
been ruled improper by the Civilian Complaint Review Board. By
Laurie Flynn.
</P>
<P>
   DAYTRADE-MARKETPLACE (Washington) _ A report by the North
American Securities Administrators Association finds that
day-trading firms mislead their investor-customers with promises of
