<P>
   LA-LIFEGUARDS (Los Angeles) _ L.A County lifeguards showed they
were no ``Baywatch'' actors, taking top honors over the weekend at
a national contest off Cape May, N.J., competing against 900
professional lifeguards. They return home and describe the tricks _
and difficulties _ of the trade at a time when some beaches are
having a tough time finding qualified lifeguards. By Steve Carney.
(Will move in the ``n'' state and ``a'' national news files.) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HACKER-COURT (Los Angeles) _ A showdown in federal court is
expected in the case of L.A. hacker Kevin David Mitnick, as he
claims he could never pay the $8 million restitution for software
theft because he is barred from using computers. The hearing caps a
years-long legal odyssey for Mitnick, who has been held in custody
longer than any hacker in the United States and the only ever
included on the FBI's top-10 most-wanted list. By Phillip Browne.
(Will move in the ``n'' state and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   BASEBALL-CARDS (Los Angeles) _ The modern baseball card is in
big trouble. That's the word from many industry analysts and
Southern California dealers who say overproduction, an investment
mentality and greed are threatening a hobby that exploded into a
billion-dollar industry in the early '90s. By Jason Takenouchi.
(Will move in the ``n'' California, ``a'' national and ``f''
financial news files.)
</P>
