<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following for
clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of Tuesday, August
10, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please call Bob
Schenet on the Post-Intelligencer's National/Foreign Desk at (206)
448-8037.
</P>
<P>
   ANIMAL-HAVEN (SULTAN, Wash.) _ On some days, Susan Michaels
fields as many as 80 calls. One caller has a tip on six ducks shot
by blow darts in Kent. Another wonders whether her sanctuary can
take two sick pygmy goats found dumped in Monroe. A third has
another problem: An abandoned rooster needs a home. Such is life at
Pasado's Safe Haven. The animal sanctuary is the first in the
Pacific Northwest for abused and neglected farm animals.
</P>
<P>
   By Rebekah Denn. (Story has moved in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-SONICS (Seattle) _ On the latest moves by the Seattle
SuperSonics.
</P>
<P>
   By Ronald Tillery. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-SEAHAWKS-KITNER (Seattle) _ Profiling Jon Kitna, starting
quarterback for the Seattle Seahawks.
</P>
<P>
   By Clare Farnsworth. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS (Seattle) _ Seattle Mariners host the Chicago White
Sox.
</P>
<P>
   By Tyler Kepner. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
