   (NYT20) THORNWOOD, N.Y. -- Aug. 09, 1999 -- BLAIR-WITCH-PROFILE,
08-09 -- Michael Williams' misery in the woods made him a ``Blair
Witch'' star. Little did he imagine that the $35,000 film by two
unknown directors with three unknown actors would earn $80 million,
be No.2 at the box office and land on this week's covers of Time
and Newsweek. ``You know what?'' asks Williams, 26. ``I'm going to
be on Jay Leno in two weeks!'' (James Estrin/New York Times Photo)
LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT19) NEW YORK -- Aug. 09, 1999 -- PATTERNS-FASHION, 08-09 --
Matthias Vriens, Armani's new creative director, is known for
having presented the vanguard of fashion and photography in Dutch
magazine. At Dutch. Vriens, 36, sought out new photographers and
typically devoted an entire issue to a single theme, like the
influence of Yves Saint Laurent. (Chester Higgins Jr./New York
Times Photo)
</P>
