<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES NAMES DARREN A. FRANK AS VICE PRESIDENT FOR
ADVERTISING SALES 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Darren A. Frank, an 18-year employee of The New York
Times who most recently was group director for technology
advertising, has been promoted to vice president for advertising
sales, effective immediately, the newspaper said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   He replaces Denise F. Warren, who was promoted to vice president
for strategic planning.
</P>
<P>
   Frank, 40, has been group director for technology advertising
since last year. Before that appointment, he was managing director
for the newspaper's telecommunications business, where the category
grew from $6 million in 1994 to $26 million in 1998 based on his
plan to capitalize on changes in the market.
</P>
