 &UR; Y2K _ &LR;  With less than five months remaining until the end of the
year, it is time for investors to think about ways to protect their
portfolios from a potential Year 2000 stock-market disaster. Not
that a disaster necessarily will happen. Experts have been working
full steam to purge the world's computer systems of all the errant
chips and software that might think 2000 is 1900. If the effort
falls short, commerce _ or much of it _ could grind to a halt.
However, most computer people and economists contend that there is
no longer any need to fear a Y2K meltdown. By Arthur M. Louis
