   SCI-SHAPE-RECOGNITION (Undated) _ Scientists have long assumed
that people must see shape in the same way at all sizes. Otherwise,
they would recognize friends or the letter ``a'' differently at
each distance or size. Yet the artist Chuck Close is exhibiting
paintings that refute this assumption, showing that size can
dramatically affect what shape we see. By Denis Pelli.
